snippet.textDisplay:
I may have been misunderstood.

What I meant what: This music video has commercial elements to it. Ask any musician in the industry what sells and if they feel passionate and enthused about producing it. Our youth is talented, don't get me wrong. But we need to recognize the right talent and shun what is unworthy. By that, I'm not saying Clinton Cerejo is unworthy. fwiw, the guy has worked with Rehman but seriously, CSI-1 was totally commercial and it sucked balls. Dont want the same with CS-II.

snippet.textDisplay: Firstly, this video needs to be titled "Sawan Khan Manganiar feat. Clinton Cerejo". All of these Goan Catholic choir artists need to go take a walk. Hindi vocals were horrible - poor diction, intonation and very western for this arrangement. At 06:40, the Ustad picks up from where Clinton left and you can immediately see how ineffective Clinton's vocals are. From 07:42 it becomes a random band experimenting. I would have loved if this video was not made out to be for the deluded youth of India.
